Storage account endpoints are URLs used to access different storage services.

Each storage account has a unique namespace.

Examples:

* Blob: https://account.blob.core.windows.net
* File: https://account.file.core.windows.net

For example, applications use these endpoints to access stored data.

A real-life use case is web apps retrieving images from blob storage.

Another example is APIs accessing file shares.

Endpoints enable secure and structured access to storage services.
